Responses.NAM1 - Response Text: I don't know. Where did you last see them?
This one knows nothing of it.
I just work here.
I would start by interrogating our most recent residents, Elmussa Damori and Irgola the Pawnbroker.
The thefts began not to long ago. Talk to Irgola and Elmussa Damori. They both moved here recently.
Someone stole some of our mining contracts, which were written on a scroll.
There have been too many thefts recently for it to be an outsider. I believe someone in town is the thief.
Find the thief and return the mining contracts to me.
Even if you found and killed the thief, you still have to bring me the Caldera mining contracts.
You already returned the missing contracts.
I've given you the key. Take the documents back to Odral, but don't tell him that it was me, all right?
Just make up some story.
Thanks, outlander.
Well, I'm glad that's settled.
This does not sound suspicious.
If you can, sweetie pie, keep the identity of the thief secret from Odral, but tell me who it is.
Will you tell me who the thief is?
Just report back to Odral, Dumpling, but don't tell him who the spy is.
It sounds like you already took care of everything, my sweet.
I wish you had spared Elmussa's life. No need to be jealous, sweetie, but I wish I knew more thieves.
You've broken the rules of House Hlaalu, sweetie. It brings tears to my eyes when I think about your disloyalty.
Maybe you can make amends and make everything better.
I did not steal the mining contracts. Look around if you want, but don't take anything.
Yes, I stole them, outlander. Guild business. If you turn me in, you'll lose standing with the Guild. The documents are in that chest on my windowsill.
Here is the key. Tell Odral that you just found the documents lying around. That fool will believe anything if you flatter him enough.
I see you've found them. Very, well, I admit it. I stole them under contract with the Thieves Guild.
Odral Helvi has abused his power and made many enemies.
Flatter him a bit, make up some story about where you found the contracts, and I'll put in a good word for you with my Guild and with House Hlaalu.
Okay, I confess. I stole them under contract with the Thieves Guild. They are in the chest on my windowsill. Here is the key.
Odral Helvi has abused his power and made many enemies.
Flatter him a bit, make up some story about where you found the contracts, and I'll put in a good word for you with my Guild and with House Hlaalu.
Why are you asking me? You have no proof.
I don't think so. You've been expelled. Until you make amends, I don't have to discuss business with you.
I see you found the missing contracts. Where did you find them?
